From: Sidharth Sankar <sidstuffhere@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 11 Mar 2026 18:57:56 +0530
Subject: fix(crypt): use -d instead of -f to check for $NEWROOT/proc
 directory

All other instances of checks for the existence of $NEWROOT/proc use
-d or at least -e, but incorrectly using -f to check for the existence
of just a file at that path would fail to exit as it should if the
directory exists.

Fixes: d0d1ea3 ("prompt the crypto disk, when asking for a password")
Signed-off-by: Sidharth Sankar <sidstuffhere@gmail.com>
Forwarded: https://github.com/dracut-ng/dracut-ng/pull/2296
---
 modules.d/70crypt/cryptroot-ask.sh | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/modules.d/70crypt/cryptroot-ask.sh b/modules.d/70crypt/cryptroot-ask.sh
index 5adb691..edae9cd 100755
--- a/modules.d/70crypt/cryptroot-ask.sh
+++ b/modules.d/70crypt/cryptroot-ask.sh
@@ -4,7 +4,7 @@ PATH=/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin
 NEWROOT=${NEWROOT:-"/sysroot"}
 
 # do not ask, if we already have root
-[ -f "$NEWROOT"/proc ] && exit 0
+[ -d "$NEWROOT"/proc ] && exit 0
 
 command -v getarg > /dev/null || . /lib/dracut-lib.sh
 
